commit.message: version -> 0.2.11.1
Remove commented-out exclusion
Don't test lts-15 on windows-latest
Comment about lack of caching on Windows
Test Stackage LTSes up to and including 21

Upgrade to actions/cache@v3

With the old version we were getting the following error on MacOS:

    /Users/runner/.stack/setup-exe-cache/x86_64-osx/Cabal-simple_6HauvNHV_3.6.3.0_ghc-9.2.8:
    startProcess: exec: invalid argument (Bad file descriptor)

The file in question turned out to not exist.  I'm not sure what was
fixed by v3 of the action but everything seems to work fine
subsequently.

Add workflow_dispatch, to be able to manually run actions

https://docs.github.com/en/actions/using-workflows/manually-running-a-workflow
Run CI on pushes of all branches

Update dummy Haddock comments to force wrapping

They need a space after them since GHC 9.0

See

* http://h2.jaguarpaw.co.uk/posts/improving-the-typed-process-documentation/
  ("Forced type signatures to wrap")

* https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/issues/23935
Pull out terminateProcess wrapper function
Remove duplication between branches

Add redundant waitForProcess to make duplication more obvious

It can never run because of the throwIO before it
